Class FibonacciHeap

  • java.lang.Object
    • datastructures.FibonacciHeap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Heap

    public class FibonacciHeap
extends java.lang.Object
implements Heap
    Fibonacci heap is a heap structure that consists a forest of trees. Compared to binomial trees the structure of this heap is more flexible. The trees do not have to be a prescribed shape. This allows postponing the work of some operations to later operations.
